課程大綱










英語口語訓練（二）（下）ENGLISH  ORAL TRAINING (2)(II)






開課系所 Department/Institute:  外文系          Foreign Languages and Literature
開課教師 Instructor:   王穎 Wang, Yin                     
開課學年 Academic Year:   0103
開課學期 Semester:    2
開課序號 Serial Number:   053

課程屬性碼 Attribute Code:   FLL 2106E
課程碼 Course Number:   B220120 
分班碼 Class Code:   2
學分數 No. of Credits:           2
課程語言 Medium of Instruction:   英文


課程網址 Course Website:         At NCKU Moodle	

先修課程或先備能力 Prerequisite Course(s): 

教師聯絡資訊 Contact with Teacher
  	    Yin Wang 
Email: yinwang@mail.ncku.edu.tw
Office Hours: Mon 3-5PM and Wed 4-5pm      

助教資訊 Contact with Tutor


學習規範 Course Policy


評量方式 Grading


方法百分比%

出席 Participation
10個人口頭報告 Presentations
60其他 others:課堂討論
30




教學方法 Teaching Strategies


方法百分比%
影音欣賞 Video/music appreciation
40討論 Discussion
40報告 Presentation
20




		※請遵守智慧財產權觀念  不得不法影印
		 Please follow the Intellectual Property instruction and No illegal copy
	

課程教材 Course Material
	    Liu, Jun, et al. Communication Strategies 4. Cengage Learning, 2008.    

參考書目 References


備註 Remarks





基本素養 Basic Literacy
□ 厚植人文素養及西洋文學、語言、文化及知識
 To cultivate their spirit of humanity and increase their knowledge of western literature, languages and cultures.
■ 培養獨立思考、團隊合作及思辨能力、發展關懷與服務精神
 To improve their capabilities for independent thinking, teamwork, and critical analysis and develop their civil concern and spirit of service
□ 擴展國際視野、接受多元文化及跨領域學習
 To broaden their global vision and accept diverse cultures and interdisciplinary 
learning.
 

核心能力 Competence
□ 具備全球視野的胸襟以及批判思維能力
 To develop global vision and critical thinking skills
□ 展現相當於全民英檢中高級複試合格的聽、說、讀、寫能力
 To show higher-intermediate level proficiency in English listening, speaking, reading and writing skills required by the GEPT exam.
■ 奠定第二外語之基礎聽、說、讀、寫能力
 Ability to demonstrate foreign language proficiency in various applications.
□ 發展團隊合作能力
 To demonstrate teamwork skills
■ 適應多元文化與職場領域的知能
 Abiltiy to accomodate diverse cultures and professional fields.
□ 培養獨立及批判性思考、提問及解決問題的能力
 Ability to think independently and critically and to raise questions and solve problems.
 

課程概述 Course Description
       加強學生英語口說流暢度、正確性，藉由多樣主題之討論活動，培養學生獨立批判性思考。The course is designed to increase your fluency, accuracy and critical thinking while discussing current issues with others in English. You will have plenty of opportunities to express your ideas in pairs, discuss them in groups and debate them in front of the whole class. You’re also responsible for encouraging others to contribute their ideas to class discussion so that you all will make progress in speaking advanced English and gaining communicative competence. You are supposed to preview the assigned readings, introduced relevant news/issues to the class and keep a voice blog for every two readings.    

課程學習目標 Course Objectives
To enhance the students' English listening and speaking abilitiesTo help the students build sustainable habits of self-learningTo improve the students' performance in professional presentations 

課程進度 Course Outline


週次 Week進度說明 Progress Description
1Course Orientation2The Devil Wears Prada (2006)3The Proposal (2009)4First Individual Presentation5Presentation Workshop6The Wolf of Wall Street (2013)7Spring Break8Second Individual Presentation9Presentation Workshop10Legally Blonde (2001)11Philadelphia (1993)12Erin Brockovich (2000)13Third Individual Presentation14Presentation Workshop15Dirty Pretty Things (2002)16Twelve Years a Slave (2013)17The Reader (2009)18Fourth Individual Presentation 

　以上每週進度教師可依上課情況做適度調整。The schedule may be subject to change.


有關課程其他調查 Other Surveys of Courses
                   1.本課程是否規劃業界教師參與教學或演講?   否            
Is there any industry specialist invited in this course? How many times? No
			
           2.本課程是否規劃內含校外實習 (並非參訪)?   否		   
Is there any in (out of) school practicum involved in this course? How many hours?  No







